$ admin.ps1

`admin.ps1`: A → Windows/PowerShell/script[PowerShell script] to become administrator (if the respective token is granted) or to query *if* the session is running with administrator privileges:

In order to query if I am running as adminstrator, the `-amI` or its → Windows/PowerShell/language/statement/function/parameters/attributes/alias[alias] `-?` must be specified.

code {
PS C\:> admin -?
False
PS C\:> admin
PS C\:> admin -?
True
code }

